Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveA 51-year-old man, Usman Madaki, who has been trekking from Bauchi to Lagos in support of the presidential ambition of Bola Ahmed, arrived in Ilorin, the capital of Kwara State on Wednesday.
In a chat with the News Agency of Nigeria, Madaki, said he commenced the trekking on June 10 and planned to arrive in Lagos on Saturday (June 25).
He said, “I want to meet Tinubu in Lagos to celebrate with him on his victory as the presidential candidate of the APC.
“I share the belief that he will be Nigeria’s next President. I like Tinubu, he is my godfather even though he doesn’t know me.”
